20his%20career%20as%20an%20assistant%20art%20director%20on%20the%20television%20film%20Tamas%20(1987).%20He%20later%20worked%20as%20an%20assistant%20art%20director%20on%20television%20series%20such%20as%20Kabir%20(1988-1990)%20and%20Chanakya%20(1991)%20before%20making%20his%20independent%20art%20direction%20debut%20on%20Chanakya%20in%201991.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDesai%20continued%20to%20work%20on%20television%20series%2C%20including%20Bharat%20Ek%20Khoj%20(1992-1993)%2C%20Kora%20Kagaz%20(1993)%2C%20and%20Swabhimaan%20(1995-1996).%20He%20made%20his%20Bollywood%20debut%20as%20an%20art%20director%20with%20the%20film%20Hum%20Dil%20De%20Chuke%20Sanam%20(1999).%20His%20other%20successful%20Bollywood%20films%20include%20Lagaan%20(2001)%2C%20Devdas%20(2002)%2C%20Swades%20(2004)%2C%20Jodhaa%20Akbar%20(2008)%2C%20and%20Prem%20Ratan%20Dhan%20Payo%20(2015).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECritics%20and%20audiences%20alike%20have%20praised%20Desai's%20work.%20He%20received%20four%20National%20Film%20Awards%20for%20Best%20Art%20Direction%20and%20three%20Filmfare%20Best%20Art%20Direction%20Awards.%20In%202016%2C%20he%20was%20awarded%20the%20Padma%20Shri%2C%20the%20fourth-highest%20civilian%20award%20in%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDesai%20founded%20ND%20Studios%2C%20a%20film%20and%20television%20production%20facility%20in%20Karjat%2C%20Maharashtra%2C%20and%20produced%20the%20film%20Desh%20Devi%20(2002).%20His%20sets%20were%20known%20for%20intricate%20detail%20and%20historical%20accuracy%2C%20creating%20some%20of%20the%20most%20iconic%20and%20memorable%20scenes%20in%20Bollywood%20history.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ctable%3E%3Cthead%3E%3Ctr%3E%3Cth%20colspan%3D%5C%222%5C%22%3EHelplines%3C%2Fth%3E%3C%2Ftr%3E%3C%2Fthead%3E%3Ctbody%3E%3Ctr%3E%3Ctd%3EVandrevala%20Foundation%20for%20Mental%20Health%3C%2Ftd%3E%3Ctd%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22tel%3A%2B919999666555%5C%22%3E9999666555%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Ahelp%40vandrevalafoundation.com%5C%22%3Ehelp%40vandrevalafoundation.com%3C%2Fa%