ps%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2022%2F10%2F12%2Fus%2Fpolitics%2Fkenneth-chesebro-trump-fake-electors.html%5C%22%3EChesebro%20has%20maintained%20a%20low%20profile%3C%2Fa%3E%20while%20his%20attorney%20argues%20he%20was%20simply%20doing%20his%20job%20as%20a%20lawyer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMuch%20of%20the%20indictment%20makes%20the%20argument%20that%20Trump%C2%A0%3Cem%3Eknew%3C%2Fem%3E%20the%202020%20election%20wasn't%20rigged%2C%20but%20that%20he%20plotted%20to%20overturn%20the%20results%20anyway.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20indictment%20doesn't%20reference%20any%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-indictment-pence-notes-evidence-election-january-6-2023-8%5C%22%3Ememos%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20text%20messages%20from%20Trump%20laying%20out%20elements%20of%20his%20plan%2C%20as%20you%20might%20expect%20in%20a%20criminal%20conspiracy%20case.%20Proving%20his%20intent%2C%20Krissoff%20said%2C%20will%20involve%20a%20lot%20of%20trial%20testimony%20from%20other%20people%20who%20were%20in%20the%20room%20with%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20case%20is%20gonna%20be%20essentially%20testimony%20based%2C%20this%20will%20require%20testimony%20of%20incredibly%20large%20number%20of%20very%20powerful%20people%2C%26quot%3B%20Krissoff%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20testimony%20of%20an%20apologetic%20co-conspirator%20who%20helped%20Trump%20out%20with%20his%20plans%3F%20All%20the%20more%20persuasive%20for%20a%20jury.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EProsecutors%20have%20struggled%20to%20get%20witnesses%20to%20flip%20against%20Trump%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20pressure%20put%20on%20Trump's%20associates%20has%20echoes%20of%20another%20criminal%20investigation%20into%20Trump%2C%20into%20his%20finances.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EManhattan%20District%20Attorney%20Alvin%20Bragg%20was%20the%20first%20prosecutor%20to%20indict%20Trump%2C%20earlier%20this%20year.%20He%20brought%2034%20counts%20of%20falsifying%20business%20records%20related%20to%20hush-money%20payments%20made%20to%20Stormy%20Daniels%20ahead%20of%20the