%E2%80%93%20With%20No%20Criminal%20Cases%20%E2%80%93%20Suspended%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F01182806%2FUntitled-design-28.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESrinagar%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Authorities%20have%20suspended%20the%20passports%20of%20some%20journalists%20and%20at%20least%20one%20political%20activist%20in%20Kashmir%20among%20others%2C%20terming%20them%20%E2%80%9Csecurity%20threats%20to%20India%E2%80%9D%2C%3Cem%3E%20The%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20can%20confirm.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInvoking%20Section%2010(3)%20of%20The%20Passports%20Act%2C%201967%2C%20the%20Regional%20Passport%20Office%20in%20Srinagar%20has%20sent%20out%20mails%20to%20at%20least%20two%20journalists%20and%20a%20political%20activist%20among%20others%2C%20informing%20them%20that%20their%20passports%20have%20been%20suspended.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESection%2010(3)%20empowers%20the%20passport%20authority%20to%20impound%20or%20revoke%20the%20passport%20of%20an%20Indian%20citizen%20if%20it%20%E2%80%9Cdeems%20it%20necessary%20so%20to%20do%20in%20the%20interests%20of%20the%20sovereignty%20and%20integrity%20of%20India%2C%20the%20security%20of%20India%2C%20friendly%20relations%20of%20India%20with%20any%20foreign%20country%2C%20or%20in%20the%20interests%20of%20the%20general%20public.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20email%2C%20which%20has%20been%20sent%20out%20from%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Apassport.admin%40passportindia.gov.in%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epassport.admin%40%3Cwbr%3Epassportindia.gov.in%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20also%20directs%20them%20to%20contact%20the%20Srinagar%20office%20on%20Boulevard%20Road%20near%20Nehru%20Park%2C%20%E2%80%9CAction%20will%20be%20taken%20against%20you%20if%20unable%20to%20contact%20before%20the%20date%20as%20mentioned%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20mail%2C%20reviewed%20by%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESrinagar%20Passport%20Officer%2C%20Devinder%20Singh%2C%20said%20that%20there%20are%20%E2%80%9Cinstructions%20from%20intelligence%20agencies%E2%80%9D%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20which%20some%20passports%20of%20Kashmiri%20residents%20are%20being%20impounded.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20have%20got%20instructions%20to%20suspend%20the%20passports%20of%20dozens%20of%20persons%20but%20I%20can%E2%80%99t%20disclose%20the%20exact%20number.%20Some%20of%20them%20have%20been%20intimated%20about%20the%20action%20being%20taken%2C%E2%80%9D%20Singh%20told%20The%20Wire%2C%20refusing%20to%20elaborate.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESources%20said%20that%20the%20list%20of%20the%20people%20whose%20passports%20are%20being%20impounded%20has%20been%20prepared%20by%20the%20central%20and%20J%26amp%3BK%20security%20agencies%20and%20it%20includes%20names%20of%20some%20journalists%2C%20academicians%2C%20lawyers%2C%20political%20activists%20and%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fmehbooba-mufti-passport-denied-national-security%5C%22%3EPassport%20Denials%20and%20Travel%20Bans%20Are%20Now%20Part%20of%20Life%20in%20J%26amp%3BK%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENo%20criminal%20cases%20against%20either%20journalist%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20list%20includes%20a%20Srinagar-based%20senior%20journalist%20who%20has%20also%20worked%20with%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Hindustan%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%20in%20New%20Delhi%20at%20the%20editor-level%20before%20shifting%20to%20Kashmir%20some%20years%20ago.%20It%20also%20includes%20a%20mid-career%20journalist%20who%20works%20with%20a%20Delhi-based%20magazine.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENone%20of%20the%20two%20journalists%2C%20whose%20passports%20have%20been%20already%20impounded%2C%20are%20accused%20in%20any%20criminal%20case%2C%20the%20journalists%20told%3Cem%3E%20The%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20and%20no%20explanation%20has%20been%20provided%20to%20them%20by%20the%20passport%20authority%20about%20the%20reason%20for%20the%20suspension%20of%20their%20passports.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20both%20of%20them%20have%20been%20questioned%20in%20the%20past%20by%20security%20agencies%20in%20connection%20with%20their%20reportage%20on%20Kashmir.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20source%20said%20that%20the%20list%20comprises%2098%20people%20from%20Kashmir.%20Another%20said%20that%20there%20were%20%E2%80%9Cmore%20than%20200%E2%80%9D%20people%20in%20the%20list.%20However%2C%20officials%20didn%E2%80%99t%20confirm%20the%20actual%20number%20of%20people%20whose%20passports%20have%20been%20or%20are%20in%20the%20process%20of%20getting%20cancelled.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Wire%20tried%20to%20reach%20out%20to%20Additional%20Director%20General%20of%20Police%20(Kashmir)%2C%20Vijay%20Kumar%2C%20on%20the%20issue.%20He%2C%20however%2C%20didn%E2%80%99t%20answer%20repeated%20calls%20and%20text%20messages.%20The%20story%20will%20be%20updated%20if%20and%20when%20he%20responds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPDP%20worker%20is%20a%20close%20aide%20of%20Waheed%20Parra%E2%80%99s%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20political%20activist%20who%20works%20with%20Peoples%20Democratic%20Party%20and%20is%20a%20close%20aide%20of%20Waheed%20Parra%2C%20the%20party%E2%80%99s%20youth%20president%2C%20is%20among%20those%20whose%20passports%20have%20been%20impounded%20by%20the%20authorities.%20The%20activist%20too%20has%20been%20termed%20a%20%E2%80%9Csecurity%20threat%20to%20India%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EParra%2C%20who%20was%20among%20the%20political%20detainees%20held%20in%20the%20aftermath%20of%20the%20reading%20down%20of%20Article%20370%20in%202019%2C%20was%20barred%20from%20leaving%20Kashmir%20and%20joining%20a%20leadership%20programme%20at%20the%20Yale%20University%20earlier%20this%20year%20by%20authorities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESources%20said%20that%20some%20journalists%20were%20also%20called%20up%20for%20questioning%20by%20J%26amp%3BK%20Police%E2%80%99s%20counter-intelligence%20unit%20in%20Srinagar%20recently.%20At%20least%20four%20journalists%2C%20who%20spoke%20with%20%3Cem%3EThe%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3EWire%3C%2Fem%3E%20on%20the%20condition%20of%20anonymity%2C%20said%20that%20the%20investigators%20asked%20them%20about%20a%20%E2%80%98Chinese%20journalist%E2%80%99%20who%20is%20believed%20to%20have%20visited%20Kashmir%20recently%20.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20was%20asked%20whether%20I%20met%20this%20Chinese%20journalist%20but%20I%20had%20no%20idea%20what%20they%20were%20talking%20about%2C%20and%20I%20told%20them%20so%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20one%20of%20the%20journalists%2C%20wishing%20to%20remain%20anonymous.%20He%20said%20that%20the%20investigators%20ran%20him%20through%20a%20questionnaire%20comprising%20dozens%20of%20%E2%80%9Cpersonal%20and%20professional%E2%80%9D%20questions%2C%20including%20details%20of%20bank%20payments%20and%20travel%20history.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAn%20ongoing%20process%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20not%20the%20first%20time%20that%20authorities%20have%20imposed%20restrictions%20on%20the%20movement%20of%20some%20Kashmiri%20activists%20and%20journalists%2C%20who%20work%20with%20national%20and%20international%20organisations.%20Free%20speech%20activists%20have%20alleged%20that%20the%20%E2%80%9Ccriminalisation%20of%20journalism%E2%80%9D%20is%20part%20of%20a%20wider%20crackdown%20on%20free%20speech%20by%20the%20Union%20government%20which%20directly%20runs%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEarlier%20this%20year%2C%20Sanna%20Irshad%20Mattoo%2C%2029%2C%20a%20Srinagar-based%20photojournalist%20and%20a%20Magnum%20Foundation%20fellow%2C%20was%20stopped%20from%20flying%20to%20the%20US%20by%20immigration%20authorities%20at%20New%20Delhi%E2%80%99s%20Indira%20Gandhi%20International%20Airport.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMattoo%2C%20who%20was%20part%20of%20the%20Reuters%20team%20that%20won%20Pulitzer%20for%20the%20coverage%20of%20the%20Covid-19%20pandemic%20in%20India%2C%20was%20earlier%20also%20stopped%20from%20flying%20to%20Paris%20where%20she%20was%20scheduled%20to%20participate%20in%20a%20book%20launch%20and%20photography%20exhibition.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fkashmiri-student-activist-waiting-for-a-passport-ten-months-after-application%5C%22%3EKashmiri%20Student%20Activist%20Waiting%20for%20a%20Passport%20Ten%20Months%20After%20Application%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEarlier%2C%20Zahid%20Rafiq%2C%20a%20Srinagar-based%20journalist%20who%20has%20worked%20with%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Hindu%20%3C%2Fem%3Eand%3Cem%3E%20Tehelka%3C%2Fem%3E%20magazine%2C%20was%20prevented%20from%20leaving%20Kashmir%20for%20a%20teaching%20fellowship%20at%20Cornell%20University%20in%20the%20United%20States.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20has%20ratified%20the%201966%20International%20Covenant%20on%20Civil%20and%20Political%20Rights.%20According%20to%20Article%2012%20of%20the%20Covenant%2C%20everyone%20has%20the%20right%20to%20leave%20any%20country%2C%20including%20their%20own.%20This%20right%20to%20travel%20is%20also%20included%20in%20Article%2021%20of%20the%20Indian%20Constitution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20least%20four%20Kashmiri%20journalists%20presently%20languishing%20in%20jail%20under%20preventive%20detention%20are%20facing%20anti-terror%20investigations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20a%20Human%20Rights%20Watch%20report%2C%20at%20least%2035%20Kashmiri%20journalists%20have%20faced%20%E2%80%9Cpolice%20interrogation%2C%20raids%2C%20threats%2C%20physical%20assault%20or%20criminal%20cases%E2%80%9D%20in%20connection%20to%20their%20work%20since%202019%20when%20the%20Union%20government%20bifurcated%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20and%20downgraded%20the%20erstwhile%20state%20into%20two%20union%20territories.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20ranking%20in%20the%202023%20World%20Press%20Freedom%20Index%20slipped%20further%20to%20161%20out%20of%20180%20countries%20from%20142%20in%202021%20and%20150%20in%202023%20with%20the%20fall%20bla