202006%2C%20which%20ultimately%20opted%20(with%20military%20backing)%20to%20govern%20for%20more%20than%20two%20years%20instead%20of%20its%20allotted%2090%20days%2C%20may%20be%20on%20such%20skeptics%E2%80%99%20minds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20old%20PTI%20has%20splintered%20under%20the%20duress%20it%20has%20faced%20since%20the%20May%209%20incident%20%E2%80%93%20where%20PTI%20protests%20nationwide%20devolved%20into%20property%20destruction%20including%20on%20military%20installations.%20Politicians%20from%20the%20PTI%E2%80%99s%20provincial%20base%20in%20Khyber%20Pakhtunkhwa%2C%20where%20the%20PTI%20has%20governed%20either%20solely%20or%20in%20coalition%20since%202013%2C%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dawn.com%2Fnews%2F1765262%5C%22%3Edefected%3C%2Fa%3E%20en%20masse%20from%20their%20former%20captain.%20These%20are%20not%20mere%20back%20benchers%20but%20include%20two%20former%20PTI%20chief%20ministers%20of%20the%20province%20and%20at%20least%20one%20former%20provincial%20cabinet%20minister.%20This%20most%20recent%20news%20merely%20adds%20to%20the%20number%20of%20PTI%20leaders%20who%20have%20opted%20to%20retire%2C%20leave%20politics%2C%20or%20switch%20parties%20%E2%80%93%20with%20others%20still%20in%20detention%20for%20their%20alleged%20roles%20in%20the%20May%209%20incident%20or%20other%20purported%20wrongdoings.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGiven%20Khan%E2%80%99s%20charisma%2C%20the%20PTI%20could%20have%20been%20organised%20around%20party%20workers%20and%20loyalists.%20But%20Khan%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jstor.org%2Fstable%2Fj.ctv10crdkk.9%5C%22%3Eopted%3C%2Fa%3E%20instead%20to%20rely%20on%20electable%20politicians%20%E2%80%93%20many%20of%20whom%20had%20switched%20parties%20repeatedly%20in%20their%20careers%20%E2%80%93%20to%20vault%20more%20quickly%20to%20national%20power%20with%20military%20support%20in%202018.%20This%20decision%20has%20been%20the%20original%20sin%20that%20has%20facilitated%20the%20party%E2%80%99s%20vulnerability%20now%20that%20it%20faces%20military%20ire.%20The%20extent%20to%20which%20Khan%20retains%20his%20enormous%20loyalty%20with%20the%20public%20is%20unclear.%20Yet%20whether%20Khan%20voters%20will%20have%20enough%20plausible%20candidates%20to%20vote%20for%20at%20the%20polls%20seems%20even%20further%20in%20doubt.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20the%202018%20PTI%20coalition%20was%20more%20fragile%20than%20it%20sometimes%20appeared%20to%20outside%20observers%20and%20PTI%20diehards.%20Winning%20less%20than%20a%20third%C2%A0of%20the%20national%20vote%20and%20with%20PTI%20requiring%20partners%20to%20secure%20a%20national%20assembly%20majority%2C%20small%20headwinds%20against%20the%20party%20always%20threatened%20it%20in%20a%20re-election.%20It%20now%20faces%20a%20gale%20from%20the%20establishment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPakistan%E2%80%99s%20predicament%20is%20considerable.%20Its%20sickly%20economy%20has%20been%20rehabilitated%20by%20currency%20infusions%20from%20the%20International%20Monetary%20Fund%20and%20rich%20Gulf%20countries%20but%20absent%20any%20meaningful%20macro-%20or%20microeconomic%20changes%20that%20will%20alter%20its%20poor%20underlying%20economic%20health.%20It%20continues%20to%20be%20vulnerable%20to%20climate-induced%20disasters.%20The%20US%20withdrawal%20from%20Afghanistan%20has%20not%20improved%20its%20security%20predicament%20as%20some%20anti-American%20Pakistani%20skeptics%20had%20suggested.%20Instead%2C%20Pakistan%20now%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dawn.com%2Fnews%2F1765402%5C%22%3Estruggles%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20a%20growing%20Afghan%20safe%20haven.%20While%20few%20expect%20the%20security%20situation%20to%20return%20to%20the%20dire%20days%20of%20the%20late%202000s%20or%20early%202010s%2C%20the%20number%20of%20attacks%20on%20the%20periphery%20has%20notably%20increased%20and%20it%20is%20a%20reasonable%20fear%20that%20core%20cities%20may%20not%20be%20far%20behind.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPakistan%E2%80%99s%20economy%20has%20flourished%20in%20the%20past%20only%20with%20international%20patronage%20%E2%80%93%20but%20the%20prospect%20for%20that%20seems%20distant%2C%20too.%20While%20international%20donors%20have%20indicated%20through%20their%20recent%20behaviour%20that%20they%20will%20not%20permit%20a%20Pakistani%20economic%20collapse%2C%20there%20is%20no%20apparent%20interest%20in%20returning%20to%20prior%20peaks%20of%20funding.%20The%20US%20is%20profoundly%20dissatisfied%20with%20its%20erstwhile%20ally.%20China%E2%80%99s%20own%20sluggish%20economy%20along%20with%20the%20poor%20performance%20of%20many%20Chinese%20projects%20in%20Pakistan%20is%20likely%20to%20slow%20substantially%20the%20macroeconomic%20impacts%20of%20Chinese%20investments%20in%20its%20all-weather%20friend.%20Many%20of%20the%20most%20capable%20Pakistanis%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftribune.com.pk%2Fstory%2F2390704%2Fcountrys-brain-drain-situation-accelerated-in-2022%5C%22%3Eleaving%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20country%20%E2%80%93%20with%20emigration%20tripling%20in%202022%20compared%20to%20(pandemic-reduced)%202020%20and%202021%20numbers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20first%20visited%20South%20Asia%20in%202002.%20At%20that%20time%2C%20according%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdata.worldbank.org%2Findicator%2FNY.GDP.PCAP.KD%3Fend%3D2022%26locations%3DPK-BD-IN%26start%3D2005%5C%22%3EWorld%20Bank%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Pakistanis%20earned%20more%20on%20average%20than%20their%20Indian%20and%20Bangladeshi%20peers.%20Since%20that%20time%2C%20the%20income%20of%20the%20average%20Pakistani%20has%20increased%20perhaps%2060%25%20in%20real%20terms.%20Yet%20in%20that%20same%20period%20the%20income%20of%20an%20average%20Indian%20has%20increased%20by%20150%25%20and%20that%20of%20the%20average%20Bangladeshi%20has%20shot%20up%20by%20more%20than%20160%25.%20The%20average%20Pakistani%20now%20makes%20the%20least%20of%20the%20big%20three%20subcontinental%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFacing%20such%20economic%20and%20political%20troubles%2C%20Pakistan%20has%20focused%20inward%20for%20the%20last%20several%20years.%20It%20pursued%20quiet%20talks%20with%20India%20that%20produced%20a%20ceasefire%20in%20February%202021%20%E2%80%93%20no%20doubt%20facilitated%20by%20India%E2%80%99s%20own%20desire%20to%20manage%20a%20growing%20China%20threat%20by%20tamping%20down%20violence%20on%20the%20Kashmir%20frontier.%20Yet%20while%20Pakistanis%20expected%20the%20ceasefire%20to%20be%20a%20prelude%20to%20bilateral%20political%20engagement%2C%20those%20subsequent%20steps%20never%20took%20place.%20The%20extent%20to%20which%20this%20was%20because%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20own%20hesitations%20or%20internal%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsouth-asia%2Fpakistan-india-modi-visit-general-bajwa-hamid-mir-journalist%5C%22%3Ecivil-military%20clashes%3C%2Fa%3E%20within%20Pakistan%20is%20not%20fully%20known.%20What%20does%20seem%20apparent%20is%20none%20of%20the%20major%20political%20or%20military%20actors%20in%20Pakistan%20is%20invested%20in%20rapprochement%20with%20India%20or%20vice%20versa.%20There%20are%20signs%20the%202021%20ceasefire%20is%20fraying%20%E2%80%93%20with%20complaints%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fradio.gov.pk%2F25-04-2023%2Farmed-forces-fully-prepared-for-befitting-response-of-any-indian-aggression-ispr%5C%22%3Eboth%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hindustantimes.com%2Fcities%2Fchandigarh-news%2Floc-infiltration-attempts-on-the-rise-army-foils-multiple-bids-seeks-to-prevent-militancy-revival-in-kashmir-101687891202355.html%5C%22%3Esides%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20adherence%20to%20the%20letter%20and%20spirit%20of%20the%20agreement%20may%20be%20less%20than%20complete.%20With%20few%20other%20avenues%20to%20signal%20displeasure%2C%20the%20ceasefire%20could%20collapse%20with%20just%20one%20large%20attack.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPakistan%20continues%20to%20exhibit%20what%20sociologist%20Laurent%20Gayer%20has%20referred%20to%20in%20other%20contexts%20as%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Fbooks%2Fedition%2FKarachi%2FBklRBAAAQBAJ%3Fhl%3Den%26gbpv%3D1%26printsec%3Dfrontcover%5C%22%3Eordered%20disorder%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9D.%20Despite%20nearly%20continuous%2C%20high-stakes%20political%20contestation%2C%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20players%20and%20the%20terrains%20of%20their%20confrontation%20have%20shown%20a%20significant%20level%20of%20continuity%E2%80%9D%20for%20decades.%20The%20same%20players%20play%20the%20same%20game%20in%20today%E2%80%99s%20Pakistan%2C%20all%20while%20the%20country%20fails%20to%20advance%20much%20even%20while%20it%20avoids%20collapse.%20None%20expect%20that%20elections%2C%20if%20they%20take%20place%20in%202023%2C%20will%20produce%20any%20meaningful%20deviation%20from%20the%20political%20status%20quo.%20Whether%20the%20PPP%20or%20PML-N%20or%20PTI%20defectors%20secure%20sufficient%20votes%20to%20head%20the%20coalition%2C%20the%20same%20personalities%20will%20play%20the%20same%20game%20of%20musical%20chairs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPakistan%20is%20stuck%2C%20and%20India%20is%20stuck%20next%20to%20Pakistan.%20It%20would%20be%20easy%20for%20observers%20in%20New%20Delhi%20to%20conclude%20that%20this%20repetitious%20mess%20should%20be%20ignored.%20Analyst%20Happymon%20Jacob%20recently%20stressed%20that%20observers%20must%20know%20that%20%E2%80%9CIndia%20is%20no%20longer%20locked%20into%20a%20strategic%20competition%20with%20Pakistan.%E2%80%9D%20India%E2%80%99s%20new%20agenda%20is%20about%20the%20Indo-Pacific%2C%20not%20Pakistan.%20This%20is%20no%20doubt%20true%20at%20some%20level%2C%20but%20it%20is%20not%20so%20easy%20to%20escape%20neighbors.%20If%20Islamabad%20and%20Rawalpindi%20conclude%20they%20have%20gained%20little%20from%20the%20ceasefire%20and%20opt%20to%20divert%20some%20of%20the%20ire%20of%20angry%20young%20Islamists%20toward%20India%2C%20Kashmir%20could%20again%20heat%20up.%20Can%20the%20Indian%20counterinsurgency%20grid%20and%20intelligence%20agencies%20quash%20such%20problems%3F%20Perhaps%2C%20but%20with%20an%20active%20China%20frontier%20and%20Manipur%20aflame%2C%20it%20is%20hardly%20a%20proposition%20that%20anyone%20should%20be%20eager%20to%20test.%20India%E2%80%99s%20capabilities%20are%20growing%20but%20they%20are%20not%20so%20great%20that%20it%20can%20easily%20manage%20trouble%20in%20the%20west%20and%20the%20east%20at%20the%20same%20time.%20That%20will%20require%20careful%20choices.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EChristopher%20Clary%20is%20an%20associate%20professor%20of%20political%20science%20at%20the%20University%20at%20Albany%2C%20State%20University%20of%20New%20York%2C%20and%20a%20nonresident%20fellow%20of%20the%20Stimson%20Center%E2%80%99s%20South%20Asia%20program%20in%20Washington%2C%20DC.%20His%20book%2C%20%3C%2Fem%3EThe%20Difficult%20Politics%20of%20Peace%3A%20Rivalry%20in%20Modern%20South%20Asia%3Cem%3E%2C%20was%20published%20by%20Oxford%20University%20Press%20in%202022.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690887648000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F01160903%2Fusama-tayyab-ivNmrA2Vg8g-unsplash.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsouth-asia%2Fpakistan-is-stuck-and-india-is-stuck-next-to-it%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22India%E2%80%99s%20capabilities%20are%20growing%20but%20they%20are%20not%20so%20great%20that%20it%20can%20easily%20manage%20trouble%20in%20the%20west%20and%20the%20east%20at%20the%20same%20time.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A19%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsouth-asia%2Fpakistan-is-stuck-and-india-is-stuck-next-to-it%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Yazidi%20genocide%20by%20Islamic%20State%20ranked%20alongside%20Holocaust%20after%20UK%20recognition%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690884180000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F23%2F08%2F768x432%2Fskynews-yazidi-islamic-state_6237018.jpg%3F20230801120027%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fyazidi-genocide-by-islamic-state-in-iraq-and-syria-ranked-