20timely%20treatment.%20At%20least%20four%20antenatal%20care%20visits%20are%20recommended%20to%20monitor%20the%20health%20of%20the%20pregnant%20woman%20and%20her%20fetus.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20rural%20areas%2C%20about%2054%20percent%20of%20mothers%20attend%20the%20recommended%20visits%2C%20compared%20to%2068.1%20percent%20in%20urban%20areas.%20This%20implies%20that%20roughly%20half%20of%20pregnant%20women%20in%20rural%20regions%20do%20not%20visit%20hospitals%20for%20advised%20care.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EConsequently%2C%20these%20complications%20significantly%20impact%20women%E2%80%99s%20lives.%20In%20India%2C%20there%20were%2097%20maternal%20deaths%20per%201%2C00%2C000%20live%20births%20reported%20between%202018%E2%80%9320.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9COne%20of%20the%20major%20reasons%20behind%20such%20deaths%20is%20that%20women%20avoid%20going%20to%20far-off%20healthcare%20centres%20for%20routine%20checkups.%20The%20complications%2C%20if%20any%2C%20remain%20ignored%2C%E2%80%9D%20Tamil%20Nadu-based%20Senthil%20Kumar%20Murugesan%20tells%20%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Better%20India%3C%2Fstrong%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CHigh-risk%20mothers%20are%20usually%20identified%20in%20the%20third%20trimester%2C%20which%20is%20around%20the%20eighth%20month%20of%20pregnancy.%20However%2C%20by%20this%20time%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20often%20too%20late%20to%20effectively%20manage%20complications%20before%20labour.%20This%20can%20lead%20to%20fatal%20outcomes.%20Currently%2C%20all%20records%20are%20maintained%20on%20paper%2C%20and%20if%20mortality%20occurs%2C%20the%20reason%20behind%20the%20death%20remains%20unknown.%20There%20are%20no%20data-based%20analyses%20available%2C%E2%80%9D%20adds%20the%2033-year-old.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Fjiovio-2-1690550162.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20